PostHarvest IQ — Alembic migrations

This project uses a hybrid schema management strategy:
- Base.metadata.create_all() in app/main.py handles initial table creation on startup.
- Alembic manages incremental schema changes after the baseline is established.

All migration operations are guarded with existence checks so they are safe to run
regardless of which bootstrap path was used.

---

New environment setup
---------------------
1. Configure your database URL in .env (DATABASE_URL).
2. Start the app once:  uvicorn app.main:app
   - create_all() creates all tables.
   - The app auto-stamps alembic_version to head (no manual step needed).
3. All future schema changes are applied with:  alembic upgrade head

Existing environment (applying migrations to a running DB)
----------------------------------------------------------
alembic upgrade head

This is safe to run at any time. Each migration checks whether its changes have
already been applied (e.g., column already exists from a prior create_all) and
skips any operations that are already in place.

Rolling back
------------
alembic downgrade -1       # one step back
alembic downgrade base     # all the way back (drops migration changes only —
                           # tables created by create_all are not removed)

Generating new migrations
-------------------------
After changing an ORM model, autogenerate a new revision:

  alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe the change"

Review the generated file before committing — autogenerate cannot detect every
change (e.g., server defaults, check constraints) and may include spurious diffs
for tables managed outside Alembic (language_admin1, language_admin2 are excluded
via include_object in env.py).

Tables intentionally outside Alembic
-------------------------------------
language_admin1 and language_admin2 have no ORM model. They are loaded and
refreshed by data/load_data.py using if_exists='replace'. Do not add them to
ORM models or generate migrations for them.
